        { "region": "South Asia — Maldives", "description": "Battuta serves as chief qazi of the Maldives for 18 months and attempts to impose stricter Islamic law on a society that maintains its pre-Islamic customs — illustrating the tension between orthodox and local-syncretic Islam across the Indian Ocean world." }
