        { "region": "Global", "description": "The Bangladesh genocide (est. 300,000–3 million killed by Pakistani forces and collaborators) produces the first post-WWII intervention on purely humanitarian grounds. India does not wait for UN approval. The precedent of state sovereignty giving way to mass atrocity prevention will be debated in international law for the next 50 years (Kosovo 1999, Libya 2011)." }
