      "systemic_insight": "The hill states' paradox: they sit on enormous water wealth (river origins, hydropower) but cannot industrialise it because terrain restricts manufacturing, and debt restricts investment. The tourism economy (sacred + scenic) is their most viable path, but both are climate-vulnerable — glacial retreat threatens water supply (Gangotri glacier retreating 22m/year), and extreme weather events (2013 Kedarnath, 2021 Chamoli glacier flood) make pilgrimage infrastructure inherently precarious."
