      "factual_description": "PUNJAB: 'Five rivers' (post-partition: Sutlej, Beas, Ravi only). Green Revolution (1960s) makes it India's bread-basket — 15% of wheat on 3% of land. Water table collapsing (3ft/year). Green Revolution's agrarian crisis: MSP dependency, groundwater depletion, soil degradation. Farm protests of 2020–21 force Central government to repeal three farm laws. Dalit population highest in any Indian state (32%). 2022: AAP wins 92/117 seats — rejection of Congress-Akali binary. HARYANA: Carved from Punjab in 1966 on linguistic grounds. Jat community (25%) is the swing vote. Gurgaon-Manesar-Faridabad belt is India's post-liberalisation manufacturing showcase — Maruti Suzuki, Hero MotoCorp, Hyundai. Jat reservation agitation (2016, violent) shows agrarian-OBC tension. DELHI: 30M+ metro population — world's second-largest urban agglomeration. No manufacturing — pure services (government, trade, IT, education). Yamuna is the capital of one of the world's most polluted rivers. Eight cities on the same site from Indraprastha (mythological) to Lutyens' New Delhi (inaugurated 1931). Air quality: India's most acute urban governance failure. LG vs elected CM constitutional tension is structurally unresolved. UTTAR PRADESH: 80 Lok Sabha seats — whoever wins UP wins India. World's oldest continuously inhabited city (Varanasi). Ayodhya Ram temple consecrated (January 22, 2024) after 500-year dispute resolved by Supreme Court (2019). Caste arithmetic: SP (Yadav+Muslim), BSP (Jatav), BJP (Brahmin+Thakur+non-Yadav OBC). BIHAR: Magadha — world's first large-scale empire from here (Pataliputra). Nalanda — world's first residential university (5th–12th century; 9 million manuscripts burned by Muhammad bin Bakhtiyar Khilji, 1193). Most complex caste coalition: RJD (Muslim+Yadav), JD-U (Kurmi+EBC), BJP (upper caste bridge). Primary economic activity: exporting labour to other states.",
