      "factual_description": "RAJASTHAN: India's largest state by area (342,239 sq km). Thar Desert (world's most densely populated desert); Aravalli range (670M years — world's oldest mountains). 19 major princely states merged in 7 stages (1948–49) by Sardar Patel — proclaimed March 30, 1949 (Rajasthan Day). Pokhran nuclear tests (1974, 1998) in Thar Desert. Economy: Tourism (5 crore+ visitors/year, 6 UNESCO sites), zinc mining (Hindustan Zinc — world's largest zinc producer), Bhadla Solar Park (world's largest solar installation, 2,245 MW), marble and granite, gem cutting. Congress-BJP strict alternation every election since 1993. GUJARAT: Longest coastline (1,600km), mercantile DNA: Lothal dockyard (world's first, 2500 BCE) → Bharuch (Rome's trade window) → Surat (Mughal India's greatest port, EIC's first Indian factory 1608) → Ahmedabad (Manchester of India) → Surat again (90% of world's diamonds cut here). State formed May 1, 1960 (Mahagujarat Movement). Amul cooperative (Anand, 1946) — White Revolution model. 2001 Bhuj earthquake (7.7M, 20,000+ dead). 2002 riots. Modi as CM 2001–2014; PM 2014–present. BJP rules continuously since 1995. GIFT City (Gujarat International Finance Tec-City) — India's offshore financial zone bid. MAHARASHTRA: India's highest state GDP. Mumbai = financial capital (BSE Asia's oldest stock exchange, RBI HQ). Pune = IT + auto manufacturing. Shiv Sena split (Uddhav vs Shinde), NCP split (Sharad vs Ajit Pawar) — most complex coalition politics in India. Maratha community (28–32%) demands OBC reservation — live constitutional crisis. Vidarbha cotton belt: 10,000+ farmer suicides per decade. GOA: 451 years of Portuguese rule (1510–1961) — longest Western colonial presence in Asia. Operation Vijay liberated in 36 hours. Baroque churches, vindaloo, Casino tourism on Mandovi river. Smallest state.",
