      "factual_description": "MADHYA PRADESH: Geographic heart of India. Vindhya range (north), Satpura range (south), Narmada between. Sanchi stupa (Ashoka, 3rd BCE), Udayagiri caves (Gupta), Khajuraho (Chandela, 10th CE — 25 of original 85 temples survive). 1984 Bhopal gas tragedy (Union Carbide methyl isocyanate leak) — world's worst industrial disaster: 15,000–20,000 killed, 500,000+ injured. Union Carbide's $470M settlement (1989) considered grotesquely inadequate; Warren Anderson never extradited. India's largest soybean producer, second in wheat. Panna — India's only diamond mine. Shivraj Singh Chouhan — India's longest-serving non-founding CM (4 terms, 2005–2023). BJP dominated since 2003 except 15-month Congress government ended by Scindia defection (2020) with 22 MLAs — most dramatic defection in Indian legislative history. CHHATTISGARH: Carved from MP in 2000 (26th state). '36 forts.' Gondwana coal (largest reserves in world). Bhilai Steel Plant (Soviet-built, 1959) as cultural identity. Naxalite heartland — Salwa Judum (2005–11 state vigilante militia) declared unconstitutional by Supreme Court. Tribal ST population: 32%. Nutrition indicators among India's worst despite mineral wealth. JHARKHAND: Chhota Nagpur Plateau — Santhal Hul rebellion (1855) led by Sido and Kanhu Murmu. Birsa Munda's Ulgulan (1895–1900). Jamshedpur — Tata Steel (1907), India's first planned industrial city. Jharia coalfields: underground fires burning 100 years. India's only uranium mine (Jaduguda). JMM (Hemant Soren) vs BJP. ST population sits atop mineral wealth but receives least of its benefits — textbook 'resource curse.'",
