      "systemic_insight": "West Bengal's 50-year decline from India's commercial capital to a state losing capital, talent, and industrial investment is the most studied regional stagnation in Indian economic history. The CPM's labour militancy — protecting existing jobs at the cost of new investment — created the conditions under which Mamata replaced them, but Mamata's even more investment-hostile political culture (Singur, Nandigram) continued the trend. The circular logic: political support comes from existing workers and farmers who fear displacement; policies protect them; no new industry enters; the state falls further behind; political mobilisation intensifies around identity rather than development. West Bengal is the cautionary tale for every Indian state that prioritises political patronage over institutional investment."
