      "systemic_insight": "India's UTs and enclaves reveal the unfinished business of colonial geography: territories whose historical accidents (Portuguese liquor tax, French architectural quarter, Le Corbusier's commission, Arab maritime trade) created administrative anomalies that persist as governance structures. Chandigarh's unresolved Punjab-Haryana dispute is the most politically consequential — a city built to replace Lahore still legally belongs to no one state, 70 years on. The enclaves demonstrate that geography inherited from colonialism does not automatically reorganise into administrative logic — it requires political will, which is often absent when every stakeholder prefers the anomaly to the resolution."
